{{Top|legends=Flier}}
{{Quote|When I was just a kid, the Blobfish bought a used flyer that he made me fix&mdash;I always could figure out how a machine fit together or why it had broken. I unclogged one of the turbojets and rebuilt the other out of scrap from the front half of an airspeeder.|Rey writing in her survival guide|<ref name="RSG">''[[Rey's Survival Guide]]''</ref>}}
'''Flyers''' were a type of vehicle that used two [[turbojet]]s and could carry multiple individuals. During the [[scavenger]] [[Rey Skywalker|Rey]]'s [[Youngling|childhood]] on the [[planet]] [[Jakku]]<ref name="RSG" /> following her arrival there in [[16 ABY]],<ref name="Timelines">''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]''</ref> the [[junk dealer]] [[Unkar Plutt]] purchased a used flyer and made her repair it. Rey unclogged one of the vehcile's turbojets and rebuilt the other using scrap from the front half of an [[airspeeder]]. Plutt then sent six [[Gender|men]] and a hired [[pilot]] in the flyer to [[Carbon Ridge]] [[mountain]] in search of its treasure. The group took two [[Death|casualties]] fighting [[dead-enders]] at the mountain and found no treasure, returning only with a stack of brittle [[stormtrooper]] [[armor]]. Rey later mentioned the incident and vehicle in a [[Rey's survival guide|survival guide]] that she wrote<ref name="RSG" /> by [[34 ABY]],<ref name="Date">''[[Rey's Survival Guide]]'' includes an addendum at the end describing some of the events of {{Film|VII}}, written several [[Standard day|days]] after they take place. The addendum is the final entry in the guide and is included chronologically after the entry mentioning the flyer. ''[[Star Wars: Timelines]]'' dates the events of the film to [[34 ABY]].</ref>

